Spam Message Detection System
# What This Project Is About
Have you ever received messages like “Congratulations! You won a prize!” or “Click this link to claim reward”?
 Most of us see these almost every day  and many of them are spam.
This project is a simple attempt to solve that real-life problem using machine learning.
It is a Python-based program that can:
Read a message
Understand its content
Predict whether it is Spam or Not Spam (Ham)
The goal of this project is not just to build something technical, but to apply what I learned in a practical and meaningful way.

# Why I Made This
Spam messages are something I personally experience a lot. Sometimes they are easy to identify, but other times they look very real and can confuse people.
While learning about machine learning, I realized this is a perfect example of how technology can help in daily life. So I built this project to:
Understand how machines process text
Learn how classification works
Solve a small but real problem

# How This Project Works
The system follows a few simple steps:
Takes a message as input
Converts the text into numerical form using TF-IDF
Uses a Naive Bayes model to classify the message
Outputs whether the message is:
✅ Not Spam (Ham)
🚫 Spam

# Technologies Used
Python
Pandas
Scikit-learn

